<task id="task-7394" class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Log in to Git account in <ph conkeyref="name-variables/ks-ped" class="- topic/ph "/></title><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><context class="- topic/section task/context "><p class="- topic/p ">If your Git personal access token expires, you can update the new token in <ph conkeyref="name-variables/ks-ped" class="- topic/ph "/>. Do as follows:</p></context><steps class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click on the dropdown of the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Profile</uicontrol> icon and choose <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Log in to Git</uicontrol>.</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><image width="400" href="../image/ks-850-pe-git.png" class="- topic/image "/></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Log in to Git</uicontrol> dialog, enter your Git <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Username</uicontrol> and Git <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Personal Access Token</uicontrol>.</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><image width="500" href="../image/ks-850-pe-log-in-to-git.png" class="- topic/image "/></info><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">Granting the Write permission for this token is recommended. You can click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Save authentication</uicontrol> to remember this credentials for the next time opening this project.</info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Log in</uicontrol>.</cmd></step></steps><result class="- topic/section task/result ">You've successfully updated your Git personal access token in <ph conkeyref="name-variables/ks-ped" class="- topic/ph "/>.</result></taskbody></task>